Package dev.arnaud

Class GraphViz

  • java.lang.Object
    • dev.arnaud.GraphViz
  • public class GraphViz
extends java.lang.Object
    Purpose: GraphViz Java API
    Description:
    With this Java class you can simply call dot from your Java programs
    Example usage: 
        GraphViz gv = new GraphViz();
    gv.addln(gv.start_graph());
    gv.addln("A -> B;");
    gv.addln("A -> C;");
    gv.addln(gv.end_graph());
    System.out.println(gv.getDotSource());

    String type = "gif";
    File out = new File("out." + type);   // out.gif in this example
    gv.writeGraphToFile( gv.getGraph( gv.getDotSource(), type ), out );
    Version:
    v0.4, 2011/02/05 (February) -- Patch of Keheliya Gallaba is added. Now you can specify the type of the output file: gif, dot, fig, pdf, ps, svg, png, etc., v0.3, 2010/11/29 (November) -- Windows support + ability to read the graph from a text file, v0.2, 2010/07/22 (July) -- bug fix, v0.1, 2003/12/04 (December) -- first release
    Author:
    Laszlo Szathmary (jabba.laci@gmail.com)
